	  "Stealthily approaching the forge, Larissa paused outside the open doorway, her nerves coiling tight in her stomach. The glow from within illuminated the intricate patterns etched onto the blade Victor meticulously finished, his fingers working with a skill and precision that stirred envy in her own soul. His voice carried across the room, deep and rich, accompanied by a rhythmic tap-tap of hammer against steel. A shiver ran down her spine as she listened, her resolve wavering slightly. Yet she knew that the time was now, or perhaps it might never come again.Taking a steadying breath, she stepped inside, determined not to falter. Her heels clicked softly against the wooden floor, echoing hollowly in the otherwise empty space. Victor glanced up from his work, his grey eyes widening briefly before settling into a familiar grin.\"Ah, there you are!\" he called out, wiping his hands on a cloth before standing to greet her.Larissa held out the bottle of wine, feeling her cheeks flush at the attention his gaze lingered on her face. \"You\'ve been working quite late, old friend.\" She attempted to hide the tremor in her voice, her eyes flickering toward the half-finished weapon before meeting his gaze once more. \"I thought this might help ease some tension from the day.\"Victor chuckled, accepting the gift graciously, and gestured towards a nearby stool. \"Thank you, dear. Have a seat and tell me, how did your travels go?\"She sank onto the offered chair, grateful for the change in subject as she poured each of them a generous serving from the bottle. Sipping slowly, she recounted their latest adventure, careful to avoid mentioning the true reason for her visit. The night wore on as they discussed old memories, new plans, and everything in between. The warmth of the alcohol loosened her tongue, but she hesitated each time the topic drifted toward the elephant in the room.Eventually, the last drop of wine drained from their glasses, the silence growing tense. Larissa swallowed nervously, gathering her courage. \"Victorâ€¦\"He paused, eyes locking onto hers expectantly.Her heart pounded wildly beneath her chest as she drew in a deep breath, fighting to find the words that had eluded her for so long. \"I wanted...to say...\"Before she could continue, the heavy doors burst open, revealing two guards bearing Tyrus\' emblem. Larissa froze, her gaze darting to the man who entered behind them. Fury seethed from his rigid stance and stern expression, dark eyebrows knitted in disapproval.\"Rune-mage Larissa Rathari, you are under arrest for suspected treason against King Prospero. Hand over your weapons and submit peacefully.\"Larissa\'s mind whirled, struggling to comprehend the accusation. In a swift movement, she grasped her warhammer, ready to defend herself and Victor alike. The night\'s delicate atmosphere crumbled, replaced by a chilling realization of what awaited them.As they dragged her away, she caught one final glimpse of Victor, his stoic expression betraying neither fear nor anger, merely understanding. She vowed silently, staring into his eyes, that they would face this challenge together, no matter the cost.\n", 
	  "*As the wooden door creaks open, light streams in from outside, casting long shadows across the dim room. Larissa pauses briefly, composing her nerves before stepping inside, clutching the two bottles tightly against her chest. Her tail swings gently behind her as she moves, a hint of playfulness in its sway.*\n\n\"Hey, Victor!\" She calls out cheerfully, hoping to hide the tremble in her voice.\nVictor looks up, his hands stained with metal filth as he wipes them on a rag. His smile lights up the place like sunshine breaking through storm clouds. \"Ah, my dear Larissa! What brings you here so late?\"\nHis warm greeting melts some of the tension in her chest. She takes a deep breath, bracing herself for what was about to come. \"Well, uh... I couldn\'t sleep last night. Thought maybe we could share a drink and talk?\" The weight of her heartbeat seemed amplified in the silence, pressing against her chest like a suffocating blanket.\n\"Of course, sit down.\" He gestures towards an old chair beside the firepit. \"And why wouldn\'t you sleep, sweetheart? Something troubling your mind?\"\nShe perches herself on the worn leather seat, placing the wine bottles on the table, avoiding his gaze. \"Yes... sort of.\" Larissa gathers her courage and finally meets his piercing eyes. \"You know how... how I feel about you?\"\nThe atmosphere crackled with tension, charged with emotions held tightly in check. Victor set down the sword and stared at her steadily, his eyebrows furrowing in confusion.\n\"Feel...?\"\n*Her fingers grip the bottle nervously, the cool glass smooth against her palm. Suddenly, everything felt so vulnerable and fragile, as though any wrong word might break it all apart.*\n\"I... I want... I want more than just friendship. With you. Maybe... something more...\"", 
